        "gold_answer": "Cataloochee",
        "level": "easy",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks about a *different* Messer Barn located in a valley in the Great Smoky Mountains of North Carolina.\nThe provided text states: \"This barn [the John Messer Barn in Sevier County, Tennessee] should not be confused with the Messer Barn in Cataloochee, which was built by John's cousin, Will Messer.\"\nIt also states: \"Cataloochee is a valley in the Great Smoky Mountains of North Carolina, located in the Southeastern United States.\"\nThus, the different Messer Barn is in the Cataloochee valley.\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[Cataloochee]"
        }
