            "thought": "Thought: The question asks for the historical name of the acid that dissolves phenazine.\nFirst, I need to identify which acid dissolves phenazine based on the context.\nThe context about Phenazine states: \"Sulfuric acid dissolves it, forming a deep-red solution.\"\nSo, the acid that dissolves phenazine is Sulfuric acid.\nNext, I need to find the historical name of Sulfuric acid.\nThe context about Sulfuric acid states: \"The historical name of this acid is oil of vitriol.\"\nTherefore, the historical name of the acid that dissolves phenazine is \"oil of vitriol\".\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[oil of vitriol]"
        }
    },
