    "5ae726a1554299572ea54738": {
        "question": "Dixit Dominus is a psalm setting by who, which was a German, later British, baroque composer who spent the bulk of his career in London, becoming well known for his operas, oratorios, anthems, and organ concertos?",
        "context": "Dixit Dominus is a psalm setting by George Frideric Handel (catalogued as HWV 232). It uses the Latin text of Psalm 110 (Vulgate 109), which begins with the words \"Dixit Dominus\" (\"The Lord Said\").\n\nGeorge Frideric (or Frederick) Handel ( ; born Georg Friedrich H\u00e4ndel ] ; 23 February 1685 (O.S.) [(N.S.) 5 March] \u2013 14 April 1759) was a German, later British, baroque composer who spent the bulk of his career in London, becoming well known for his operas, oratorios, anthems, and organ concertos. Handel received important training in Halle and worked as a composer in Hamburg and Italy before settling in London in 1712; he became a naturalised British subject in 1727. He was strongly influenced both by the great composers of the Italian Baroque and by the middle-German polyphonic choral tradition.",
        "gold_answer": "George Frideric Handel",
        "level": "easy",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks to identify the composer of \"Dixit Dominus\". The context provides two pieces of information.\n1.  \"Dixit Dominus is a psalm setting by George Frideric Handel\".\n2.  The second paragraph describes \"George Frideric (or Frederick) Handel\" as \"a German, later British, baroque composer who spent the bulk of his career in London, becoming well known for his operas, oratorios, anthems, and organ concertos\".\nThe question combines these two pieces of information: \"Dixit Dominus is a psalm setting by who, which was a German, later British, baroque composer who spent the bulk of his career in London, becoming well known for his operas, oratorios, anthems, and organ concertos?\"\nThe \"who\" in the question refers to the composer of Dixit Dominus, and the description following \"who\" matches the description of George Frideric Handel.\nTherefore, the answer is George Frideric Handel.\n\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[George Frideric Handel]"
        }
    },
