    "5ab3f9b95542992ade7c6f09": {
        "question": "It Takes a Family is a response to this 1996 book that was published by who",
        "context": "It Takes a Family is a 2005 book by then Pennsylvania Senator Rick Santorum. The title is a response to the 1996 book \"It Takes a Village\" by then-First Lady Hillary Clinton. In the book, Santorum states that the family structure is necessary. He argues that liberal social policies have devastated the family structure and that prevailing socially liberal attitudes have systematically devalued families across the board. He argues that government should take a proactive role in promoting strong families.\n\nIt Takes a Village: And Other Lessons Children Teach Us is a book published in 1996 by First Lady of the United States Hillary Rodham Clinton. In it, Clinton presents her vision for the children of America. She focuses on the impact individuals and groups outside the family have, for better or worse, on a child's well-being, and advocates a society which meets all of a child's needs.",
        "gold_answer": "Hillary Rodham Clinton",
        "level": "hard",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks who published the 1996 book that \"It Takes a Family\" is a response to.\nThe context provides information about two books: \"It Takes a Family\" and \"It Takes a Village\".\nThe context explicitly states: \"It Takes a Family is a 2005 book by then Pennsylvania Senator Rick Santorum. The title is a response to the 1996 book 'It Takes a Village' by then-First Lady Hillary Clinton.\"\nIt also states: \"It Takes a Village: And Other Lessons Children Teach Us is a book published in 1996 by First Lady of the United States Hillary Rodham Clinton.\"\nSo, the 1996 book is \"It Takes a Village\", and it was published by Hillary Rodham Clinton.\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[Hillary Rodham Clinton]"
        }
    },
