    "5a827a9f55429940e5e1a8cf": {
        "question": "Kiawah Island, South Carolina was mentioned in \"Porgy and Bess,\" composed by the man best known for which other 1924 orchestral composition?",
        "context": "Kiawah is a sea island, or barrier island, on the Atlantic coast of the United States. Located 25 mi southwest of Charleston in Charleston County, South Carolina, it is operated today largely as a gated beach and golf resort\u2014the Kiawah Island Golf Resort\u2014with spacious villas, beaches, large and acclaimed golf courses, and other attractions. As of the 2010 census, Kiawah Island's population was 1,626, up from 1,163 at the 2000 census. The island is part of the Charleston-North Charleston-Summerville metropolitan area. Alternative spellings and variants of the name itself include \"Kiawa\", \"Kittiwar\" (in DuBose Heyward's novel \"Porgy\"), and \"Kittiwah\" (in George Gershwin's opera \"Porgy and Bess\").\n\nGeorge Jacob Gershwin ( ; September 26, 1898 July 11, 1937) was an American composer and pianist. Gershwin's compositions spanned both popular and classical genres, and his most popular melodies are widely known. Among his best-known works are the orchestral compositions \"Rhapsody in Blue\" (1924) and \"An American in Paris\" (1928) as well as the opera \"Porgy and Bess\" (1935).",
        "gold_answer": "Rhapsody in Blue",
        "level": "medium",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks about the composer of \"Porgy and Bess\" and another of his famous 1924 orchestral compositions.\n1.  Find who composed \"Porgy and Bess\". The context states, \"...'Kittiwah' (in George Gershwin's opera 'Porgy and Bess').\" and \"George Jacob Gershwin... was an American composer... Among his best-known works are... the opera 'Porgy and Bess' (1935).\" So, George Gershwin composed \"Porgy and Bess\".\n2.  Find another 1924 orchestral composition by George Gershwin for which he is best known. The context states, \"Among his best-known works are the orchestral compositions 'Rhapsody in Blue' (1924) and 'An American in Paris' (1928)...\"\n3.  The question asks for the 1924 composition. \"Rhapsody in Blue\" was composed in 1924.\n4.  The question also states \"Kiawah Island, South Carolina was mentioned in 'Porgy and Bess'\". The context confirms this: \"Alternative spellings and variants of the name itself include 'Kiawa', 'Kittiwar' (in DuBose Heyward's novel 'Porgy'), and 'Kittiwah' (in George Gershwin's opera 'Porgy and Bess').\"\n\nTherefore, Kiawah Island was mentioned in \"Porgy and Bess,\" composed by George Gershwin, who is also known for the 1924 orchestral composition \"Rhapsody in Blue.\"\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[Rhapsody in Blue]"
        }
    },
