    "5ab4280b554299233955003a": {
        "question": "Where is the globe that succeeded the Globe of Peace as the world's largest rotating globe located?",
        "context": "The Globe of Peace (Mappamondo della Pace in Italian) is a very large globe located in Apecchio, Pesaro, Italy. It was the Guinness Book of World Records record holder for the world's largest rotating globe until 1999, when it was succeeded by Eartha. It was built over a period of six years by Orfeo Bartolucci with the stated goal of diffusing a message of peace and liberty to all people. It measures 10 metres in diameter and is reported to weigh 170 quintals, which probably translates to 17,000 kilograms. Reportedly 250 quintals of putty, 30 cubic metres of wood, and a ton (unclear whether English or Metric) of nails were used in its construction. The globe is located outdoors and has a fibreglass skin. It can hold approximately 600 people and internally contains descriptive tables listing every country of the world and their flag.\n\nEartha is the world's largest rotating and revolving globe, located within the headquarters of the DeLorme mapping corporation in Yarmouth, Maine. The globe weighs approximately 5,600 pounds (2,500 kg), and has a diameter of over 41 feet (12.5 m).",
        "gold_answer": "Yarmouth, Maine",
        "level": "medium",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks for the location of the globe that succeeded the Globe of Peace. The context states, \"The Globe of Peace... was the Guinness Book of World Records record holder for the world's largest rotating globe until 1999, when it was succeeded by Eartha.\" Then, the context about Eartha states, \"Eartha is the world's largest rotating and revolving globe, located within the headquarters of the DeLorme mapping corporation in Yarmouth, Maine.\" Therefore, the successor globe, Eartha, is located in Yarmouth, Maine.\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[Yarmouth, Maine]"
        }
    },
