        "context": "Sir Adrian Cedric Boult, CH ( ; 8 April 1889 \u2013 22 February 1983) was an English conductor. Brought up in a prosperous mercantile family, he followed musical studies in England and at Leipzig, Germany, with early conducting work in London for the Royal Opera House and Sergei Diaghilev's ballet company. His first prominent post was conductor of the City of Birmingham Orchestra in 1924. When the British Broadcasting Corporation appointed him director of music in 1930, he established the BBC Symphony Orchestra and became its chief conductor. The orchestra set standards of excellence that were rivalled in Britain only by the London Philharmonic Orchestra (LPO), founded two years later.\n\nThe Royal Opera House is an opera house and major performing arts venue in Covent Garden, central London. The large building is often referred to as simply \"Covent Garden\", after a previous use of the site of the opera house's original construction in 1732. It is the home of The Royal Opera, The Royal Ballet, and the Orchestra of the Royal Opera House. Originally called the Theatre Royal, it served primarily as a playhouse for the first hundred years of its history. In 1734, the first ballet was presented. A year later, Handel's first season of operas began. Many of his operas and oratorios were specifically written for Covent Garden and had their premieres there.",
        "gold_answer": "The Royal Opera House",
        "level": "medium",
        "type": "bridge",
        "generated_trace": {
            "thought": "Thought: The question asks about a venue where Adrian Boult conducted, which is also known as \"Convent Garden\".\nFirst, I need to identify if Adrian Boult conducted at a venue with a similar name.\nThe context about Adrian Boult states: \"early conducting work in London for the Royal Opera House\".\nNext, I need to check if the Royal Opera House is also called \"Convent Garden\".\nThe context about The Royal Opera House states: \"The large building is often referred to as simply \"Covent Garden\"\".\nThe question has a slight misspelling (\"Convent Garden\" instead of \"Covent Garden\").\nSo, Adrian Boult conducted for the Royal Opera House, which is also called \"Covent Garden\".\n",
            "answer": "Action: Finish[The Royal Opera House]"
        }
    },
