        "question": "Both the Drever and Finnish Hound are two dog breeds that are bred for what purpose?",
        "context": "The Drever is a breed of dog, a short-legged scenthound from Sweden used for hunting deer and other game. The Drever is descended from the Westphalian Dachsbracke, a type of German hound called \"Bracke\". The breed name Drever was chosen through a contest in 1947.\n\nThe Finnish Hound (suomenajokoira, Finnish Bracke) is a breed of dog originally bred for hunting hare and fox.",
        "gold_answer": "bred for hunting",
        "level": "hard",
        "type": "comparison",
